<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-24T11:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-24T11:41:00-05:00" n="1542" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1542">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/67.</note>
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-24T10:00:00-06:41">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your July 23, 3 p.m. Proper representations were made several days
                                ago regarding the Christian Brothers. At present the Brothers at the
                                other points named are not yet within the jurisdiction of the
                                Carrancistas but attention has been called to them in accordance
                                with the Department’s instructions.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>